questions.query: Telegram Handle We Can Use To Contact You
Link to your Public Group Chat
Have you participated in a previous Gitcoin Grants Round? If so, please name the rounds or link the builder profile to prior rounds.
How does your project contribute significantly to the Ethereum network's infrastructure? Please provide specific examples and metrics if available.
questions.explanation: We build a protocol multi-branched git-inspired edit-centric publishing protocol whose data-layer is anchored in Ethereum (or EVM-compatible L2s).

questions.query: Describe any pioneering development work in your project, particularly in enhancing privacy, interoperability, or user experience.
questions.explanation: We have spend some time discussing various solutions about using diversified anchoring, where merkle roots can be stored in any one of a given set of networks. Also we are thinking about social identity and key recovery concepts, where private keys are trustlessly spread across contributors of the platform and they are incentivized to return the information to recover the key. This is currently sought as a standalone feature.

questions.query: What specific problems or challenges in the Ethereum ecosystem does your project address? How does your solution improve upon existing alternatives?
questions.explanation: We believe that Ethereum ecosystem can be strengthened by diversifying its utility. Currently the utility is heavily skewed towards DeFi. Whilst solutions for decentralized publishing exist, they are either standalone blockchains like gosh, that are not leveraging the security and versatility of Ethereum, or they are token-centric DAOs that tokenize research products, but not the iterative process.

questions.query: Outline your project's roadmap and how the grant funds will be used to achieve your development goals.
questions.explanation: We have been pivoting towards a new approach: Users can interact with Lakat on multiple branches, like on git, that all share a set of contributors. Private keys can be recovered socially whereby the other branch contributors act as guardians and are incentivized to contribute to the recovery process. We aim to finish this piece in April/May and integrate it into the existing lakat-protocol. In May/June we update the user-facing interface build on top (as an extension) of media-wiki and disseminate in academic institutions over the summer and autumn months.

questions.query: How does your project contribute to the decentralization and security of the Ethereum network?
questions.explanation: By anchoring the data-layer of Lakat into Ethereum we diversify the applications that are rooted in the network.
